values: So why the bleep bleep didn't my editing work.  Last entry (In Dreams) makes me sound like a moron.  Well, I am, but was hoping to keep that to myself.  Anyway, did try to edit errors but they didn't take.  Advice, please!  And, can I edit what's already posted.  Got to keep that moronic quality private!!!

I really need analysis!  Had another one of those unexplainable dreams just before waking.  I hesitate to use "bizarre", as the subject does refer to upcoming events, but it's just the way I seem to come up with the content that I find almost fascinating in a twisted kind of way!

Again I dreamed of AlliG's wedding. Apparently, in my dream it was a "destination" wedding, that being Hawaii!  Okay; love Hawaii, so that seemed to fit.  But then it gets straaaaange! We were at the airport -- Ken and I, and even Ron and Nancy, waiting to board a plane.  We were standing in a lineup to first go through Customs (?), and the lineup was kind of lounging and leaning against a dusty car, on which we wrote our names to indicate our position within the line (told you it was strange!).  Suddenly it dawned on me I forgot to pack clothes.  I had a suitcase full of toiletries but nothing to wear.  I told everyone I was going to grab a cab, rush home and pack some clothing.  Ron said his car was already parked and couldn't drive me but I told him not to worry and to stay in line.

I rushed into the Sasktel building, which for some reason was right there at the airport and went to a lineup of telephones on a countertop to call a cab.  SaskTel and none of the phones would work!  An employee finally came up to me and asked if he could help.  I told him I desperately needed a cab to get me home and back within a couple hours when my plane was taking off.

All I remember next is that I started wondering what I would pack as I had no clothes for Hawaii that would fit, but decided I would diet on the flight there and just pack whatever I had!!  Yeah, like that was going to work.

And then I woke.  Damn.  Would love to have been in Hawaii again -- even if only in dreams!

Like I said -- get me to a shrink.  Or, better yet -- wish I could shrink.  Got to get some clothes that fit.  Or better yet, fit into the clothes I've already got.

You know, I think I may be analyze this one on my own.  Think I'll keep my analysis to myself though.  Already revealed too much.

And I didn't even eat pizza before bedtime!!!!!!!!
!

Well, that didn't work!  Just lost my oh so creative ramblings.  Will try again.  What I did say, or tried to, was first to say job well done!  Pictures are soooooo pretty.  Then went on about loving Friday nights.  It is Friday night.  Fridays always have their own feeling.  And sound.  Especially at night.  Can almost hear the Phil Collins soundtrack.  Maybe even some Janet Jackson (no, not her fan, but do like the R&B sound on Friday nights.)  When I was young -- make that VERY young -- I use to dream of flying on a magic carpet over the city lights on a wintery Friday night.  The snow would be sparkling on rooftops and spirals of smoke would be rising in the air.  Now that I am no longer young -- uh, make that VERY young -- I still dream of swirling over the city, but now I'm flying in a magic Lazy-Boy!!!  Maybe that SHOULD read "no longer young"!!

Welcome to my Live Journal. As you can see it has finally become my own. The background was a gift from <lj user="owls_dream">, a surprise I didn't even know about until I clicked on it just now. Hope you love it.
